# ============================================================
# ORGANIZATION CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: organization
scope: organization.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for organization.

## policy_rules
Organization policy constrains:
- who may create organization structures
- who may join or operate within them
- what authority members may exercise
- what organization detail may be disclosed
- what must be restricted or denied

## required_behavior
- membership eligibility must be explicit
- role eligibility must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- authority boundary must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public organization summary
- member-scoped detail
- operator-scoped detail
- reviewer-scoped detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow membership only for valid scope
- allow role action only for valid authority
- allow bounded disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden authority widening
- deny out-of-scope organization action

## escalation_rules
If membership scope,
role scope,
authority boundary,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the organization path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- membership policy is explicit
- role policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- escalation rules are explicit
